  "text": "The PWWP domain is exclusively found in eukaryotes, ranging from lower eukaryotes such as protozoa and yeast to men. The human genome encodes more than 20 PWWPcontaining proteins, which are located in the nucleus and play a major role in cell division, growth, and differentiation. They are implicated in various chromatin functions, including DNA modification, repair, and transcriptional regulation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
